$ Excel Object Model: Application.wait

 `Application.wait` can be used to wait (other → development/languages[programming languages] call it sleep) until a specific time is reached.

gh|about-MS-Office-object-model|/Excel/Application/wait.bas||

Unfortunately, `application.wait` is not available in → Microsoft/Office/Word/Object-Model/Application[Word's `application` object].


sa:

  → Microsoft/Office/Excel/Object-Model/Application/onTime[`application.onTime`] allows to schedule the exeuction of a → development/languages/VBA/language/subs-and-functions[procedure].

  The → Windows/development/WinAPI function → development/languages/VBA/Win-API/examples/Sleep[Sleep].

  The → Microsoft/Office/Excel/Object-Model/Application[`application` object].
